description: Last Wednesday, President Donald Trump made it clear: Elon Musk is in charge of DOGE. But on Tuesday, Amy Gleason was named DOGE acting administrator.
title: DOGE has a new 'acting administrator,' but Elon Musk is still in charge

description: A small Ohio municipality has apologized for not publicly responding to neo-Nazi demonstrators, some holding flags with swastikas, who marched in town recently, and ordered an independent review of how police handled the matter.
title: Ohio town orders review of police response to neo-Nazi demonstrators

description: The Trump administration is planning a nationwide operation to locate and possibly deport unaccompanied migrant children.
title: Trump admin planning operation to find and possibly deport unaccompanied migrant children

description: Three-time WNBA champion and two-time WNBA Finals MVP Diana Taurasi announced her retirement from professional basketball Tuesday.
title: WNBA legend Diana Taurasi announces retirement

description: Russian officials proposed to Trump administration officials an agreement for the U.S. to make money off critical minerals and metals under Moscow’s control.
title: Russia offered U.S. a deal for minerals in Ukranian territory it seized

description: Federal workers say Elon Musk's slash-and-burn approach to the federal government is it less efficient and driving away some of the most talented people.
title: 'Absolute chaos': DOGE sows turmoil in its quest for 'efficiency'

description: As a measles outbreak sweeps through Texas, anti-vaccine groups are pushing a familiar and false theory: The virus is being caused by the vaccine itself.
title: Anti-vaccine movement falsely blames measles shots for Texas outbreak

description: U.S.  District Judge Jamal Whitehead found President Donald Trump's day one order likely exceeded his authority.
title: Judge blocks Trump order that paused refugee admissions

description: A good samaritan returned one of the bulldog puppies that was stolen from a Denver-area pet store last week in a brazen heist caught on camera, authorities said Tuesday.
title: Bulldog puppy stolen in fake seizure heist is found and returned to Colorado pet store

description: McDonald's is leaning into its reputation as a breakfast value offering, vowing to reject a surcharge on meals with eggs while announcing a special one-day discount on Egg McMuffins.
title: Bucking trend, McDonald's vows no egg surcharges as it preps $1 Egg McMuffin Day

description: Video captures the moment a Southwest Airlines plane attempted to land, narrowly missing a private jet on the runway. The NTSB and FAA are investigating the incident, stating that the Southwest flight executed a go-around after an unauthorized business jet entered the runway.
title: Southwest plane narrowly avoids collision with jet at Chicago airport

description: A woman whose 6-year-old son was fatally stabbed in an attack that prosecutors say was motivated by hate said her son watched in fear as she was stabbed.
title: Mother testifies her Palestinian American son watched as attacker stabbed her before killing boy

description: Idaho prosecutors want to present an FBI-constructed 3D model of the home where four college students were found brutally stabbed to death in 2022 at the suspect's trial this summer.
title: FBI is building a 3D model of home where Idaho college murders occured for trial

description: A New Hampshire woman was arrested on Friday for allegedly contaminating items at a grocery store with her urine over the course of several years and posting videos of it online, police said.
title: New Hampshire woman contaminated grocery store items with urine for years, police say

description: Elon Musk's status as the world's wealthiest person is in no danger of changing.
title: Musk loses more than $100B as Tesla gives up trillion-dollar company status amid sell-off

description: Twenty-one employees resigned from the United States Digital Service in protest of the Department of Government Efficiency’s effort to carry out layoffs and its communications with federal employees via email. NBC News’ Vaughn Hillyard reports on what the former USDS workers said in a letter posted online.
title: 21 former USDS employees resign in refusal to work for DOGE

description: A Missouri woman who initially pleaded not guilty to federal charges related to an elaborate scam to steal the Graceland estate from Elvis Presley’s family is now accepting some responsibility.
title: Missouri woman pleads guilty in scheme to steal Graceland

description: Utah is gearing up to make history as the first state to ban fluoride in public water systems if Gov.
title: Utah set to become first state to ban fluoride in public water

description: Laid-off employees who hung a U.S. flag upside-down at Yosemite National Park say the action was a call to protect the nation's public lands.
title: Fired Yosemite workers say upside-down U.S. flag was a call to protect public lands

description: A cargo container and makeshift office for centuries-old whiskey maker Buffalo Trace slid into the Kentucky River on Monday in the wake of heavy rains and flooding, officials said.
title: Office of Buffalo Trace whiskey distillery swept into Kentucky River by mudslide

description: A North Carolina substitute teacher has been charged with involuntary manslaughter in connection with the deaths of two teenage boys who died in an ATV crash last year, authorities announced.
title: N.C. substitute teacher charged in ATV crash that killed 2 high school football players

description: Apple shareholders rejected a proposal to eliminate internal programs intended to boost the diversity of the company's workforce on Tuesday before its public shareholder meeting.
title: Apple shareholders reject ban on diversity programs

description: Consumers grew more pessimistic about the economic outlook in February as worries brewed about a slowing economy and rising inflation, the Conference Board reported Tuesday.
title: February consumer confidence posts biggest drop since 2021 in latest sign of slowing economy

description: Direct-to-consumer footwear brand Rothy’s just recorded its best year on record after the company appointed retail veteran Jenny Ming, one of the co-founders of Old Navy, as its CEO.
title: How digitally native companies like Rothy's are growing profitably in a new era for retail

description: Elon Musk and allies have portrayed DOGE as if no one has been hunting for waste or inefficiency, but the GAO is the government's established chief watchdog.
title: The government's chief watchdog goes to Capitol Hill for first time in DOGE era

description: The Supreme Court threw out murder conviction against an Oklahoma death row inmate because a witness in the case lied in court and prosecutors withheld information about him. MSNBC's Lisa Rubin reports on Richard Glossip's case.
title: Supreme Court throws out Oklahoma death row inmate's conviction

description: Authorities in Texas said they thwarted a "mass casualty attack"and arrested a 21-year-old on charges of making terroristic threats against Corpus Christi police.
title: 21-year-old accused of planning 'mass casualty attack' on Texas police

description: The Crypto ATM Fraud Prevention Act proposed by Sen. Dick Durbin would prevent new users from spending more than $2,000 in a day at a bitcoin ATM.
title: To fight scams, Senate bill would limit transactions at crypto ATMs

description: Jon Stewart may have gotten himself more than just a wee bit too worked up while hosting “The Daily Show” on Monday.
title: Jon Stewart takes on DOGE and makes some 'cuts' of his own

description: Though still in critical condition with double pneumonia, Pope Francis is up and out of bed after a full night of rest, with his doctors saying that the mild kidney failure is no longer a concern. Meanwhile, prayers are intensifying in St. Peter’s Square with cardinals in Rome leading the first nightly rosary for the pontiff. NBC’s Anne Thompson reports for TODAY from the Vatican.
title: Pope Francis shows 'slight improvement,' Vatican says

description: House Speaker Mike Johnson and Republicans are looking to vote this week on a budget resolution in-line with President Donald Trump’s agenda. NBC News’ Julie Tsirkin reports on how some GOP lawmakers are pleading that Medicaid and Medicare not be cut.
title: Johnson hopes to hold House budget vote this week

description: While the divide between the United States and key allies grows over support for Ukraine, President Donald Trump appears focused on terms of a deal that are favorable for Russia. NBC’s Peter Alexander reports for TODAY.
title: Divide with key allies grows over Trump deal that favors Russia

description: There is growing confusion for federal employees as government leaders tell their staff they shouldn’t answer Elon Musk’s email ordering them to justify their job or face termination. The office that sent the email says responses are voluntary, but a new order from Musk makes it clear they're obligated to comply. “Failure to respond a second time will result in termination,” Musk posted on X. NBC’s Ryan Nobles reports for TODAY.
title: Confusion grows over Elon Musk demanding employee justification

description: A robotic moon lander is about to launch on a SpaceX rocket. It's the second lunar mission for a private company that last year became the first to successfully land on the moon’s surface.
title: A new lunar lander is set to launch to the moon's south pole this week

description: “Beyond the Gates,” CBS's new daytime soap opera premiering this week, is the first all-Black daytime soap on TV.
title: 'Beyond the Gates' is making Black history at a critical time on screen and off

description: A judge previously ruled the former Trump attorney had defamed Ruby Freeman and her daughter, Wandrea “Shaye” Moss by falsely claiming they committed election fraud in 2020.
title: Rudy Giuliani satisfies judgment in defamation case brought by former Georgia election workers

description: The remains of a United Kingdom man missing for nearly two-and-a-half years have been found in a privately owned wooded area near Kingsland, Georgia, the FBI said.
title: Remains of U.K. man missing for more than 2 years found in Georgia woods, FBI says

description: A California woman who admitted killing her estranged husband more than two decades ago and is now wanted in the fatal stabbing of her wife is being sought by federal authorities, a law enforcement official said Monday.
title: Woman who admitted killing previous partner is on the run after fatal stabbing of firefighter wife

description: A man is fighting to get a Social Security number and birth certificate for his toddler, Caroline — whose name is listed in state records as “Unakite Thirteen Hotel.”
title: Nebraska father in limbo after daughter’s name incorrectly listed as 'Unakite Thirteen Hotel'

description: Dan Bongino, the conservative podcaster named deputy director of the FBI, has spent the past seven years publicly criticizing the agency he will now help run.
title: Dan Bongino's yearslong history of FBI criticism and conspiracy theories

description: Three thieves staged a seizure to divert attention from the theft of two 11-month-old bulldog puppies from Perfect Pets in Centennial, Colorado. Police arrested one suspect while the two other men are still at large.
title: Thieves caught on camera stealing bulldog puppies in Colorado

description: President Trump praised Elon Musk’s demand for federal workers to outline in an email what they accomplished last week – or face dismissal. But there is also confusion after the Trump administration tonight said the request by the Office of Personnel Management was “voluntary”. NBC News’ Gabe Gutierrez reports.
title: Deadline looms for federal workers over Musk’s demand

description: President Trump met with France’s President Macron regarding the war in Ukraine. Trump is pushing for a deal to access Ukraine’s minerals as a way to repay the U.S. for billions of dollars in military aid to Ukraine. Macron warned that any peace deal would require U.S. security guarantees for Ukraine. NBC News’ Richard Engel reports.
title: Trump says peace deal to end war in Ukraine could happen 'within weeks'
